Þú getur notað tegundakerfið `typeof` til að finna tegund gildis. Til að prenta út tegund gildis þarf að nota `console.log` með tegundakerfinu sem argument.

Hér er dæmi um hvernig á að nota þetta:
```typescript
function printType(value: any): void {
  console.log(`The type of ${value} is ${typeof value}.`);
}

const number = 42;
printType(number); // The type of 42 is number.

const string = "Hello, world!";
printType(string); // The type of Hello, world! is string.
```

You can use the following C++ program to read a text file line by line and count the occurrences of a specified word in the file:

```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <string>

int main() {
    std::string filename, word;
    std::cout << "Enter the name of the text file: ";
    std::cin >> filename;
    std::cout << "Enter the word to count: ";
    std::cin >> word;

    int count = 0;
    std::ifstream infile(filename);
    if (!infile) {
        std::cerr << "Error opening file." << std::endl;
        return 1;
    }
    std::string line;
    while (std::getline(infile, line)) {
        size_t pos = 0;
        while ((pos = line.find(word, pos)) != std::string::npos) {
            ++count;
            ++pos; // skip the found word so that it's not counted twice
        }
    }
    infile.close();
    std::cout << "The word '" << word << "' appears " << count << " times in the file." << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```

